                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d431">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Ambassador</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-08-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 16, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The extradition provisions of the Revised Statutes are extended to the Philippine
                    Islands by the act of February 6, 1905, Statutes at Large, volume 33, page 698;
                    it provides that extradition to and from the islands shall be made pursuant to
                    provisions of regular extradition treaties between the United States and other
                    countries.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
